attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, Renesas SH, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This RISC-V ELF binary is a botnet agent, likely a variant of Mirai or Gafgyt. Key indicators include the use of '/tmp/.bot_lock' for process synchronization, extensive process enumeration through '/proc/%s/cmdline' and '/proc/%s/exe', and network state monitoring via '/proc/net/tcp'. The binary contains hardcoded HTTP request templates (GET, POST, HEAD) with spoofed User-Agents (e.g., Chrome 58 on Windows), commonly used for DDoS attacks. It also fingerprints the host system using '/sys/class/dmi/id/product_name' and references common system daemons like 'sshd' and 'systemd-journald', suggesting process killing or evasion capabilities.
